==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Soberly
<hw>So"ber*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a sober manner; temperately;
cooly; calmly; gravely; seriously.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Soberly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Soberly
<hw>So"ber*ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Grave; serious; solemn;
sad.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[He] looked hollow and thereto <qex>soberly</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sober-minded</ent>⟦br⟧
